[SN]TITLE[SN]
Adam Hammill: Barnsley offer new deal to winger following promotion

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Barnsley have offered a new deal to winger Adam Hammill following their League One play-off final win.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The 28-year-old scored at Wembley as the Tykes beat Millwall 3-1 on Sunday, and also scored in their Johnstone's Paint Trophy final win.
The club have also offered new deals to defenders Aidy White, 24, and George Williams, 23.
Midfielder Jak McCourt, 20, has been released after making two appearances for the club.
